ns × ~$5-10 each = $240-480 wasted on fixing the same bug\n4. Root cause: Ralph reads sprint-state.json at startup, caches it in memory, and writes back stale state after each session — overwriting the fixes made by the session itself\n5. Fix needed: Ralph needs a sprint-complete exit condition that checks if all stories are `done` before spawning a new session\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md — if it already exists, append with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"ac46f162fd905558c","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Retrospective for session 64 appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-28.md`.\n\nKey numbers:\n- **Sprint:** 74/74 stories, 17/17 epics — 100% complete\n- **Total cost:** $745.95 across 5,462 API calls ($3.60/story avg)\n- **Wasted on state corruption:** ~$240-480 across 48 no-op sessions (32-64% of total spend)\n- **Root cause:** Ralph has no sprint-complete exit condition and overwrites on-disk state with stale in-memory data after each session\n- **Top action:** Kill Ralph. The sprint is done."}],"totalDurationMs":66473,"totalTokens":29650,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1936,"cache_read_input_tokens":27525,"output_tokens":188,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1936},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
